  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      To investigate whether the administration of Glucerna achieves less glycaemic variability,
      defined as the mean absolute glucose (MAG) change, and better glycaemic control compared to a
      standard high-carbohydrate enteral formula. Continuous glucose monitoring technology will be
      used to evaluate glycaemic variability and glycaemic control.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
